**: world\n- **Username**: root\n- **Password**: root123\n\n## Reports Available\n1. **Report1**: All countries by population (descending)\n2. **Report2**: All cities by population (descending)\n3. **Report3**: All capital cities by population (descending)\n4. **Report4**: Top N cities by population (user input required)\n5. **Report5**: Population distribution by country (cities vs non-cities)\n6. **Report6**: Population distribution by region (cities vs non-cities)\n7. **Report7**: Total world population\n8. **Report8**: Population of specific area (user input required)\n9. **Report9**: Language population statistics (Chinese, English, Spanish, Urdu)\n\n## Next Steps\n- Test all reports by uncommenting them in App.java\n- Add error handling for database connections\n- Create unit tests for each report\n- Add logging for better debugging"}","mcp_server_name":"","mcp_tool_name":""}},{"id":2,"type":0,"content":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive README file to explain how to use Docker with your project:
