 45	```bash
 46	# Build and start containers
 47	docker-compose up --build -d
 48	
 49	# Check container status
 50	docker ps
 51	
 52	# View application output
 53	docker logs worldreports-app
 54	
 55	# View MySQL logs
 56	docker logs mysql
 57	```
 58	
 59	## What Happens When You Run
 60	1. **MySQL Container**: Starts with world database automatically loaded
 61	2. **Java App Container**: Builds your application and connects to MySQL
 62	3. **Database Loading**: world.sql file is automatically imported
 63	4. **Report Generation**: Currently runs Report9 (Language Population)
 64	
 65	## Troubleshooting
 66	
 67	### If containers don't start:
 68	```bash
 69	docker-compose down
 70	docker-compose up --build
 71	```
 72	
 73	### If database connection fails:
 74	```bash
 75	# Check if MySQL is ready
 76	docker logs mysql
 77	
 78	# Restart the app container
 79	docker-compose restart worldreports-app
 80	```
