Path: README-Docker.md
 1	# WorldReportsApp - Docker Setup Guide
 2	
 3	## Overview
 4	یہ application World database کے ساتھ مختلف population reports generate کرتی ہے۔ اب یہ Docker کے ساتھ MySQL database کے ساتھ چل سکتی ہے۔
 5	
 6	## Prerequisites
 7	- Docker Desktop installed
 8	- Docker Compose installed
 9	
 10	## Project Structure
 11	```
 12	WorldReportsApp/
 13	├── src/main/java/com/set08103/
 14	│ ├── App.java # Main application
 15	│ ├── DBConnection.java # Database connection
 16	│ ├── Report1_CountriesByPopulation.java # Countries by population
 17	│ ├── Report2_CitiesByPopulation.java # Cities by population
 18	│ ├── Report3_CapitalCitiesByPopulation.java # Capital cities
 19	│ ├── Report4_TopNCitiesByPopulation.java # Top N cities
 20	│ ├── Report5_PopulationDistributionByCountry.java
 21	│ ├── Report6_PopulationDistributionByRegion.java
 22	│ ├── Report7_TotalWorldPopulation.java # World population
 23	│ ├── Report8_PopulationOfArea.java # Area population
 24	│ └── Report9_LanguagePopulation.java # Language statistics
 25	├── Abdullah Uk/world-db/world.sql # World database dump
 26	├── Dockerfile # Java app container
 27	├── docker-compose.yml # Multi-container setup
 28	└── pom.xml # Maven configuration
 29	```
 30	
 31	## How to Run
 32	
 33	### Method 1: Using Batch Script (Windows)
 34	```bash
 35	run-docker.bat
 36	```
 37	
 38	### Method 2: Using Shell Script (Linux/Mac)
 39	```bash
 40	chmod +x run-docker.sh
 41	./run-docker.sh
 42	```
 43	
 44	### Method 3: Manual Commands
 45	```bash
 46	# Build and start containers
 47	docker-compose up --build -d
 48	
 49	# Check container status
 50	docker ps
 51	
 52	# View application output
 53	docker logs worldreports-app
 54	
 55	# View MySQL logs
 56	docker logs mysql
 57	```
 58	
 59	## What Happens When You Run
 60	1. **MySQL Container**: Starts with world database automatically loaded
 61	2. **Java App Container**: Builds your application and connects to MySQL
 62	3. **Database Loading**: world.sql file is automatically imported
 63	4. **Report Generation**: Currently runs Report9 (Language Population)
 64	
 65	## Troubleshooting
 66	
 67	### If containers don't start:
 68	```bash
 69	docker-compose down
 70	docker-compose up --build
 71	```
 72	
 73	### If database connection fails:
 74	```bash
 75	# Check if MySQL is ready
 76	docker logs mysql
 77	
 78	# Restart the app container
 79	docker-compose restart worldreports-app
 80	```
 81	
 82	### To run different reports:
 83	Edit `App.java` and uncomment the report you want to run:
 84	```java
 85	public static void main(String[] args) {
 86	 Report1_CountriesByPopulation.generate(); // Uncomment this
 87	 // Report9_LanguagePopulation.generate(); // Comment this
 88	}
...
 122	
 123	## Reports Available
 124	1. **Report1**: All countries by population (descending)
 125	2. **Report2**: All cities by population (descending)
 126	3. **Report3**: All capital cities by population (descending)
 127	4. **Report4**: Top N cities by population (user input required)
 128	5. **Report5**: Population distribution by country (cities vs non-cities)
 129	6. **Report6**: Population distribution by region (cities vs non-cities)
 130	7. **Report7**: Total world population
 131	8. **Report8**: Population of specific area (user input required)
 132	9. **Report9**: Language population statistics (Chinese, English, Spanish, Urdu)
 133	
 134	## Next Steps
 135	- Test all reports by uncommenting them in App.java
 136	- Add error handling for database connections
 137	- Create unit tests for each report
 138	- Add logging for better debugging
